paradise_test
Class TreeMapPriorityQueue

java.lang.Object
  paradise_test.TreeMapPriorityQueue
All Implemented Interfaces:
ModelContext, PriorityQueue
abstract class TreeMapPriorityQueue
extends java.lang.Object
implements PriorityQueue

Implements a priority queue containing ParadiseSubProblems. Nodes with higher priority will be returned before nodes with lower priority. This priority queue will be an implementation of a 2-red-black tree. Obtaining the element of highest priority can be done in constant time in this tree.

Author:
Victor Almeida Campos (campos@lia.ufc.br)

TreeMapPriorityQueue

protected TreeMapPriorityQueue(java.lang.String name,
                               ModelEmulator modelEmu,

Constructs a new, empty priority queue, sorted according to the given comparator. All keys inserted into the priority queue must be mutually comparable by the given comparator: comparator.compare(k1, k2) must not throw a ClassCastException for any keys k1 and k2 in the priority queue. If the user attempts to put a key into the priority queue that violates this constraint, the put(Object key, Object value) call will throw a ClassCastException.

Parameters:
name - the comparator that will be used to sort this priority queue. A null value indicates that the keys' natural ordering should be used.

TreeMapPriorityQueue

protected TreeMapPriorityQueue(java.lang.String name,
                               ModelEmulator modelEmu)
Constructs a new, empty priority queue, sorted according to the keys' antural order. All keys inserted into the priority queue must implement the Comparable interface. Furthermore, all such keys must be mutually comparable: comparator.compare(k1, k2) must not throw a ClassCastException for any keys k1 and k2 in the priority queue. If the user attempts to put a key into the priority queue that violates this constraint, the put(Object key, Object value) call will throw a ClassCastException.

Parameters:
name - the comparator that will be used to sort this priority queue. A null value indicates that the keys' natural ordering should be used.

Binds an internal uses port, specified by its name, to a provides port of another model represented by a specified uses port object. This specified uses port object should be created by the model driver of this component as a result of a request originated at the session handler. This method is used by the model driver's implementation of its bindPorts method.
